{"word":"στερρός","slug":"στερρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>στερρός</b></el> <el>(στερρός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <a href='S:στερεός'><el>στερεός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>stiff, firm, solid, strong</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>: <i>stiff</i> with age, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>hard, rugged, uneasy</i>, <el>λέκτρα</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>stubborn, obdurate, hard</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <el>στερρῶς</el>, <i>stiffly, obstinately</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}